verses.text_plain: Ye are the children of the Lord your God: ye shall not cut yourselves, nor make any baldness between your eyes for the dead.
verses.verse_html: 1Ye are the children of the Lord your God: ye shall not cut yourselves, nor make any baldness between your eyes for the dead.

verses.text_plain: For thou art an holy people unto the Lord thy God, and the Lord hath chosen thee to be a peculiar people unto himself, above all the nations that are upon the earth.
verses.verse_html: 2For thou art an holy people unto the Lord thy God, and the Lord hath chosen thee to be a peculiar people unto himself, above all the nations that are upon the earth.

tokens.text: unto himself, above all the nations

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not eat any abominable thing.
verses.verse_html: 3Thou shalt not eat any abominable thing.

verses.text_plain: These are the beasts which ye shall eat: the ox, the sheep, and the goat,
verses.verse_html: 4These are the beasts which ye shall eat: the ox, the sheep, and the goat,

verses.text_plain: The hart, and the roebuck, and the fallow deer, and the wild goat, and the pygarg, and the wild ox, and the chamois.
verses.verse_html:
5The hart, and the roebuck, and the fallow deer, and the wild goat, and the pygarg, and the wild ox, and the chamois. ▼
▼ pygarg: or bison: Heb. dishon

footnotes.body_html: ▼ pygarg: or bison: Heb. dishon

verses.text_plain: And every beast that parteth the hoof, and cleaveth the cleft into two claws, and cheweth the cud among the beasts, that ye shall eat.
verses.verse_html: 6And every beast that parteth the hoof, and cleaveth the cleft into two claws, and cheweth the cud among the beasts, that ye shall eat.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless these ye shall not eat of them that chew the cud, or of them that divide the cloven hoof; as the camel, and the hare, and the coney: for they chew the cud, but divide not the hoof; therefore they are unclean unto you.
verses.verse_html: 7Nevertheless these ye shall not eat of them that chew the cud, or of them that divide the cloven hoof; as the camel, and the hare, and the coney: for they chew the cud, but divide not the hoof; therefore they are unclean unto you.

tokens.text: Nevertheless these ye shall not eat

verses.text_plain: And the swine, because it divideth the hoof, yet cheweth not the cud, it is unclean unto you: ye shall not eat of their flesh, nor touch their dead carcase.
verses.verse_html: 8And the swine, because it divideth the hoof, yet cheweth not the cud, it is unclean unto you: ye shall not eat of their flesh, nor touch their dead carcase.

tokens.text: unto you: ye shall not eat

verses.text_plain: These ye shall eat of all that are in the waters: all that have fins and scales shall ye eat:
verses.verse_html: 9These ye shall eat of all that are in the waters: all that have fins and scales shall ye eat:

verses.text_plain: And whatsoever hath not fins and scales ye may not eat; it is unclean unto you.
verses.verse_html: 10And whatsoever hath not fins and scales ye may not eat; it is unclean unto you.

verses.text_plain: Of all clean birds ye shall eat.
verses.verse_html: 11Of all clean birds ye shall eat.

verses.text_plain: But these are they of which ye shall not eat: the eagle, and the ossifrage, and the ospray,
verses.verse_html: 12But these are they of which ye shall not eat: the eagle, and the ossifrage, and the ospray,

tokens.text: of which ye shall not eat

verses.text_plain: And the glede, and the kite, and the vulture after his kind,
verses.verse_html: 13And the glede, and the kite, and the vulture after his kind,

verses.text_plain: And every raven after his kind,
verses.verse_html: 14And every raven after his kind,

verses.text_plain: And the owl, and the night hawk, and the cuckow, and the hawk after his kind,
verses.verse_html: 15And the owl, and the night hawk, and the cuckow, and the hawk after his kind,

verses.text_plain: The little owl, and the great owl, and the swan,
verses.verse_html: 16The little owl, and the great owl, and the swan,

verses.text_plain: And the pelican, and the gier eagle, and the cormorant,
verses.verse_html: 17And the pelican, and the gier eagle, and the cormorant,

verses.text_plain: And the stork, and the heron after her kind, and the lapwing, and the bat.
verses.verse_html: 18And the stork, and the heron after her kind, and the lapwing, and the bat.

verses.text_plain: And every creeping thing that flieth is unclean unto you: they shall not be eaten.
verses.verse_html: 19And every creeping thing that flieth is unclean unto you: they shall not be eaten.

tokens.text: unto you: they shall not be eaten

verses.text_plain: But of all clean fowls ye may eat.
verses.verse_html: 20But of all clean fowls ye may eat.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not eat of any thing that dieth of itself: thou shalt give it unto the stranger that is in thy gates, that he may eat it; or thou mayest sell it unto an alien: for thou art an holy people unto the Lord thy God. Thou shalt not seethe a kid in his mother’s milk.
verses.verse_html: 21Ye shall not eat of any thing that dieth of itself: thou shalt give it unto the stranger that is in thy gates, that he may eat it; or thou mayest sell it unto an alien: for thou art an holy people unto the Lord thy God. Thou shalt not seethe a kid in his mother’s milk.

tokens.text: any thing that dieth of itself

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt truly tithe all the increase of thy seed, that the field bringeth forth year by year.
verses.verse_html: 22Thou shalt truly tithe all the increase of thy seed, that the field bringeth forth year by year.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt eat before the Lord thy God, in the place which he shall choose to place his name there, the tithe of thy corn, of thy wine, and of thine oil, and the firstlings of thy herds and of thy flocks; that thou mayest learn to fear the Lord thy God always.
verses.verse_html: 23And thou shalt eat before the Lord thy God, in the place which he shall choose to place his name there, the tithe of thy corn, of thy wine, and of thine oil, and the firstlings of thy herds and of thy flocks; that thou mayest learn to fear the Lord thy God always.

verses.text_plain: And if the way be too long for thee, so that thou art not able to carry it; or if the place be too far from thee, which the Lord thy God shall choose to set his name there, when the Lord thy God hath blessed thee:
verses.verse_html: 24And if the way be too long for thee, so that thou art not able to carry it; or if the place be too far from thee, which the Lord thy God shall choose to set his name there, when the Lord thy God hath blessed thee:

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou turn it into money, and bind up the money in thine hand, and shalt go unto the place which the Lord thy God shall choose:
verses.verse_html: 25Then shalt thou turn it into money, and bind up the money in thine hand, and shalt go unto the place which the Lord thy God shall choose:

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt bestow that money for whatsoever thy soul lusteth after, for oxen, or for sheep, or for wine, or for strong drink, or for whatsoever thy soul desireth: and thou shalt eat there before the Lord thy God, and thou shalt rejoice, thou, and thine household,
verses.verse_html:
26And thou shalt bestow that money for whatsoever thy soul lusteth after, for oxen, or for sheep, or for wine, or for strong drink, or for whatsoever thy soul desireth: and thou shalt eat there before the Lord thy God, and thou shalt rejoice, thou, and thine household, ▼
▼ desireth: Heb. asketh of thee

footnotes.body_html: ▼ desireth: Heb. asketh of thee

verses.text_plain: And the Levite that is within thy gates; thou shalt not forsake him; for he hath no part nor inheritance with thee.
verses.verse_html: 27And the Levite that is within thy gates; thou shalt not forsake him; for he hath no part nor inheritance with thee.

tokens.text: him; for he hath no part

verses.text_plain: At the end of three years thou shalt bring forth all the tithe of thine increase the same year, and shalt lay it up within thy gates:
verses.verse_html: 28At the end of three years thou shalt bring forth all the tithe of thine increase the same year, and shalt lay it up within thy gates:

verses.text_plain: And the Levite, (because he hath no part nor inheritance with thee,) and the stranger, and the fatherless, and the widow, which are within thy gates, shall come, and shall eat and be satisfied; that the Lord thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hand which thou doest.
verses.verse_html: 29And the Levite, (because he hath no part nor inheritance with thee,) and the stranger, and the fatherless, and the widow, which are within thy gates, shall come, and shall eat and be satisfied; that the Lord thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hand which thou doest.
